column5: Definitely looks like a head turner and would love to know the price if/when it comes out  Wonder what the tow capacity is on this and how hard it would be to modify it for camping.  http://theawesomer.com/toyotas-ultimate-utility-vehicle/326032/
Definitely a head turner. Nothing you can't customize yourself with a few 10,000 bills. For the soccer Mom that trains MMA.
Meh, look at the clearance.  Shnazzy vehicle though
Best thing is Toyota will buy you another one when the frame rots out.
Will they buy me a Chevy?
Looks like a Minivan painted flat back with fancy wheels to me.
it's a Sienna on a Tacoma 4 by frame. I've seen uglier vehicles than this haha
That's what you end up with after 11 recalls on a sienna.  Still no spare though, they still haven't figured that one out
My new rig. Pulls the lund deep v like a charm!?
I've been in bigger golf carts. That would be fun to drive on the 401. I wonder if it will do 55KPH?  M2B2, I'm feeling better. Nice story post was when I wasn't, you understand. AOD.

The ultimate kid-hauler. I'd buy one... of course that's forgetting about the whole middle part where I do not have that kind of money to spend. For now I'll just jam some hockey pucks under my Corolla's struts.
Not a van fan but it is a head turner for sure, looks bullet proof
